The company SocialBuddy SAS, hereinafter referred to as "
SWELLO
" or "
We
", is concerned about the protection of the personal data of visitors and users, hereinafter referred to as the "
User
", of its website
https://swello.com
, hereinafter referred to as the "
Site
", and is committed to protecting them in compliance with the applicable regulations, in particular Regulation (EU) No. 2016/679 of April 27, 2016, known as the "General Data Protection Regulation" or "GDPR," and Law No. 78-17 of January 6, 1978, as amended, known as the "Data Protection Act" (together hereinafter referred to as the "
Applicable Regulation on the Protection of Personal Data
").
SWELLO carries out data processing for which it is qualified as a "joint controller of processing," jointly responsible with its professional Clients. In this sense, SWELLO provides a service to Clients for which the usage will be carried out by Users. SWELLO also carries out personal data processing as the sole Data Controller. These processing activities are indicated by the abbreviation "RT" in the table presented in Article 1 of this Policy.
It is specified that SWELLO conducts an activity entirely aimed at professional clients (B2B activity). Social media accounts that may be linked to the use of the User's Account (the "
Account
") are not intended to be personal accounts. It is also specified that the Site is not intended for minors.
